            "answer_text": "Yes to both. There\u2019s no such thing as \u201cjust a theory\u201d in science. People without a scientific education frequently think \u201cjust a theory\u201d means \u201clittle more than scientific speculation\u201d. In science, a \u201ctheory\u201d is the highest graduation point. Contrary to doofuses, theories don\u2019t graduate to laws. A law, is a mathematically explained fundamental function of a given aspect of the universe. A theory explains the complex interactions of nature. A theory explains how germs work, how gravity works and how tectonic plates move. Black Holes are real. Theories explain how they work. ",
