                "name": "Eli Mendez",
                "href": "/profile/Eli-Mendez-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Yes. Black holes are a theory which has so much evidence as to be considered very likely to exist. Science has two categories of things which are considered true: direct observations and well-tested theories. Like many things in physics (such as electrons or gravity) black holes can't be observed directly, only their effects can be observed, therefore they can only ever be a theory. Using the phrase \u201conly a theory\u201d or something to that effect shows a gross lack of understanding of how science works. ",
